# Copy to .dev.vars (gitignored) and fill in real values.

# HS256 secret for the session JWT cookie. Any long random string locally;
# production uses `npx wrangler secret put SESSION_SECRET`.
SESSION_SECRET=dev-only-secret-change-me

# When set, outgoing mail (including magic links) is logged to the console
# instead of sent. Leave on for local development.
EMAIL_DEV_LOG=1

# When set, local dev auto-authenticates as this admin address (no magic link).
AUTH_DEV_BYPASS_EMAIL=admin@example.com

# Database backend for local dev: "d1" (default) or "supabase". With "supabase"
# the worker reads/writes Postgres over the HYPERDRIVE binding instead of D1.
# DB_BACKEND=d1

# Stripe keys for the giving module (Supabase backend only). The secret key
# authorizes Checkout/Portal/subscription API calls; the webhook secret verifies
# inbound Stripe events at /api/stripe/webhook. Use test-mode keys locally
# (sk_test_… / whsec_…); production uses `wrangler secret put`. Both unset →
# giving checkout/webhook are inert.
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxx
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx

# Local Supabase/Postgres uses the canonical host environment variable below. It is
# consumed by Wrangler before Worker bindings load, so it MUST NOT be placed in
# `.dev.vars`. Export it in the host shell that starts `npm run dev` instead:
# export CLOUDFLARE_HYPERDRIVE_LOCAL_CONNECTION_STRING_HYPERDRIVE='postgres://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/postgres'
# See docs/supabase-setup.md. No assignment is included here intentionally.

# Token for the nightly D1→R2 backup (src/lib/backup.ts). Set this plus the
# CF_ACCOUNT_ID + D1_DATABASE_ID vars in wrangler.jsonc to enable backups; if
# any is unset the backup cron skips gracefully. Production uses
# `wrangler secret put D1_EXPORT_TOKEN`.
# D1_EXPORT_TOKEN=
